# Test-First (Red → Green → Refactor)

## Default workflow

- Start by writing or updating a failing test that captures the intended behavior (or acceptance criterion).
- Then implement the smallest change to make the test pass.
- Refactor only after tests are green.

## Coverage expectations

- Prefer a mix of:
  - Unit tests for services/utils (`tests/unit/**`)
  - Integration tests for routes and flows (`tests/integration/**`, Supertest)
- If a change is tied to `specs/prd-001.md` acceptance criteria, add/adjust test coverage for that criterion in the same PR.

## Definition of done for a feature change

- `npm test` passes.
- At least one integration test covers the primary happy-path workflow (when applicable).
